  "prompt": "What is the best time table for a student of maths and science of class 11th?",
  "response": "Creating an effective timetable for a Class 11 student focusing on Maths and Science involves balancing study time, breaks, and other activities to ensure overall well-being and academic success. Here's a suggested weekly timetable that you can adjust based on your specific needs and schedule:\n\n### Daily Schedule\n\n#### Morning\n- **6:30 AM - 7:00 AM:** Wake up and freshen up\n- **7:00 AM - 7:30 AM:** Light exercise or yoga\n- **7:30 AM - 8:00 AM:** Breakfast\n- **8:00 AM - 9:00 AM:** Review previous day's notes (any subject)\n\n#### School Hours\n- **9:00 AM - 3:30 PM:** School (assuming a typical school day)\n\n#### Afternoon/Evening\n- **3:30 PM - 4:00 PM:** Snack and relax\n- **4:00 PM - 6:00 PM:** Study Session 1\n  - **Monday, Wednesday, Friday:** Mathematics\n  - **Tuesday, Thursday:** Physics\n- **6:00 PM - 6:30 PM:** Break\n- **6:30 PM - 8:30 PM:** Study Session 2\n  - **Monday, Wednesday, Friday:** Physics\n  - **Tuesday, Thursday:** Chemistry\n  - **Saturday:** Mathematics\n- **8:30 PM - 9:00 PM:** Dinner\n- **9:00 PM - 10:00 PM:** Leisure time (hobbies, relaxation)\n- **10:00 PM - 10:30 PM:** Prepare for the next day, set goals\n- **10:30 PM:** Bedtime\n\n#### Weekly Adjustments\n- **Saturday:**\n  - **Morning:** Follow the usual routine\n  - **4:00 PM - 6:00 PM:** Study Chemistry\n  - **6:30 PM - 8:30 PM:** Study Biology (if applicable) or extra practice on any subject\n- **Sunday:**\n  - **Morning:** Light revision of the week's topics\n  - **Afternoon:** Family time, hobbies, or rest\n  - **Evening:** Leisure activities, relaxation\n\n### Tips for Effective Studying\n1. **Active Learning:** Use techniques like summarizing, questioning, and teaching the material to someone else to deepen understanding.\n2. **Regular Breaks:** Follow the Pomodoro Technique (25 minutes of focused study followed by a 5-minute break) to maintain concentration.\n3. **Variety in Study Material:** Mix different types of problems and resources to keep the study sessions engaging.\n4. **Regular Revision:** Allocate time each week to revisit and revise old material to reinforce learning.\n5. **Practice:** Regularly solve problems in Maths, Physics, and Chemistry to build confidence and skill.\n6. **Seek Help:** Don\u2019t hesitate to ask teachers or peers for help when you're stuck.\n\n### Subject-Specific Tips\n- **Mathematics:** Focus on understanding concepts deeply and practice regularly. Work on different types of problems to build versatility.\n- **Physics:** Emphasize understanding the principles and their applications. Solve numerical problems and conceptual questions.\n- **Chemistry:** Divide your time between physical, inorganic, and organic chemistry. Use diagrams and mnemonics to remember reactions and structures.\n\nRemember, this is a general template. You should feel free to adjust the timings and subjects according to your school's schedule and personal learning pace. The key is to maintain consistency and ensure you're not overwhelming yourself.",
